name: ethanone, 1-phenyl-, oxime

We might estimate the oxime addition to contribute around +60 to the melting point because of its ability to form strong intermolecular hydrogen bonds. Considering the combined effects of increased polarity and potential for intermolecular bonding, the numbers can be somewhat synergistic. Nonetheless, assigning a strict numerical value to each is not completely straightforward without empirical data, but we can approximate based on known effects of similar functional groups.
